\frac12 r 
\sin (\theta)
x = \frac12 r \cos( \theta ) , \quad y = r \sin( \theta )
x(r,\theta)=\dfrac r 2\cos(\theta)
y(r,\theta)=r\sin(\theta)
r,\theta
\begin{cases}  \dfrac{\partial x}{\partial r}(r,\theta)= \dfrac 1 2\cos(\theta),& \dfrac{\partial x}{\partial \theta}(r,\theta)=-\dfrac r 2\sin(\theta)\\ \dfrac{\partial y}{\partial r}(r,\theta)=\sin(\theta), & \dfrac{\partial y}{\partial \theta}(r,\theta)=r\cos(\theta) \end{cases}
\left|\begin{matrix}\dfrac{\partial x}{\partial r}(r,\theta) & \dfrac{\partial x}{\partial \theta}(r,\theta)\\ \dfrac{\partial y}{\partial r}(r,\theta) & \dfrac{\partial y}{\partial \theta}(r,\theta) \end{matrix}\right| = \left|\begin{matrix}\dfrac 1 2\cos(\theta) & -\dfrac r 2\sin(\theta)\\ \sin(\theta) & r\cos(\theta) \end{matrix}\right|=\dfrac r 2.
|J|= \left| \begin{array}{ccc} D_1x & D_2x  \\ D_1y & D_2y \\  \end{array} \right|= \left| \begin{array}{ccc} \frac 1 2 \cos(\theta) & - \frac 1 2 r\sin(\theta)  \\  \sin(\theta) & r\cos(\theta)  \\ \end{array} \right|= \frac 1 2 r
